;Draft notes
*{{note label|Note1|a|a}}The [[Chicago Blackhawks]]' first-round pick went to San Jose Sharks as the result of a trade on June 27, 2014, that sent a first-round pick in 2014 (27th overall) and the Rangers sixth-round pick in 2014 (179th overall) to Chicago in exchange for a first-round pick in 2014 (20th overall) and this pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Blackhawks select Schmaltz in first round of the 2014 NHL draft and acquire picks from San Jose|url=http://blackhawks.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=724253&navid=DL|date=June 27, 2014|accessdate=June 27, 2014}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note1|b|b}}The [[Pittsburgh Penguins]]' second-round pick went to the San Jose Sharks as the result of a trade on March 25, 2013, that sent [[Douglas Murray (ice hockey)|Douglas Murray]] to the Penguins in exchange for a [[2013 NHL Entry Draft#Round two|2013 second-round pick]] (#58–[[Tyler Bertuzzi]]) and this conditional pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Penguins Acquire Defenseman Douglas Murray from San Jose in Exchange for a 2013 Second-Round Draft Pick and a 2014 Conditional Second-Round Draft Pick  – Pittsburgh Penguins – News|url=http://penguins.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=662036|publisher=Pittsburgh Penguins|date=March 25, 2013}}</ref>
**'''Condition''' – Second-round pick if Penguins advance to third round of 2013 playoffs or if Murray re-signs with Penguins for 2013–14 season, else third-round pick. Converted to third-round pick when Penguins were eliminated in second-round of 2013 playoffs and Murray signed with the [[Montreal Canadiens]] on August 22, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=August 22, 2013 – Montréal Canadiens – News|url=http://canadiens.nhl.com/club/blogpost.htm?id=19707|publisher=''Montreal Canadiens''|date=August 22, 2013}}</ref>
*The San Jose Sharks' fourth-round pick went to the Edmonton Oilers as the result of a trade on October 21, 2013, that sent [[Mike Brown (ice hockey, born 1985)|Mike Brown]] to the Sharks in exchange for this pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharks Acquire Forward Mike Brown from Edmonton|url=http://sharks.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=687884&navid|publisher=[[San Jose Sharks]]|date=October 21, 2013|accessdate=May 19, 2014}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note1|c|c}}The [[New York Rangers]]' fifth-round pick went to the San Jose Sharks as the result of a trade on April 2, 2013, that sent [[Ryan Clowe]] to the Rangers in exchange for a [[2013 NHL Entry Draft#Round two|2013 second-round pick]] (#49–[[Gabryel Paquin-Boudreau]]), a [[2013 NHL Entry Draft#Round three|2013 third-round pick]] (#62–[[Yan-Pavel Laplante]]) and this conditional pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharks Trade Clowe to Rangers for Three Draft Picks|url=https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/story/?id=419716|accessdate=April 2, 2013}}</ref>
**'''Condition''' – Second round if Rangers advance to third round of 2013 playoffs or if Clowe re-signs with Rangers after 2013 season, else fifth round. Converted on July 5, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Clowe Signs Five-Year, $24.25 Million Contract with Devils|url=https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/story/?id=427017|date=July 5, 2013|accessdate=July 5, 2013}}</ref>
*The San Jose Sharks' fifth-round pick went to the [[Chicago Blackhawks]] as the result of a trade on June 30, 2013, that sent Anaheim's fourth-round pick in [[2013 NHL Entry Draft|2013]], and a fifth-round pick in 2013 to the Sharks in exchange for a fourth-round pick in 2013 and this pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Canucks-Devils trade highlights day of deals at draft|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=675991|publisher=[[National Hockey League]]|accessdate=May 19, 2014|date=June 30, 2013}}</ref>
*The San Jose Sharks' seventh-round pick went to the [[Detroit Red Wings]] as the result of a trade on June 10, 2012, that sent [[Brad Stuart]] to the Sharks in exchange for [[Andrew Murray (ice hockey)|Andrew Murray]], and this conditional pick.<ref name="StuartSharks">{{cite news|last=St. James|first=Helene|title=Red Wings trade Brad Stuart to San Jose for Andrew Murray, draft pick|url=http://www.freep.com/article/20120610/SPORTS05/120610016/Red-Wings-trade-Brad-Stuart-to-San-Jose-for-Andrew-Murray-draft-pick|accessdate=May 19, 2014|newspaper=[[Detroit Free Press]]|date=June 10, 2012}}</ref>
**'''Condition''' – If Stuart re-signs with Sharks. Converted on June 18, 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sharks ink D Stuart to three-year, $10.8 million deal|url=https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/story/?id=398651|accessdate=June 18, 2012|newspaper=[[Total Sports Network]]|date=June 18, 2012}}</ref>

